fscDdmAgentBuild.name: fscDdmAgentBuild
fscDdmAgentBuild.description: DuplexDataManager SNMP agent build date and time.

fscDdmLastDate.name: fscDdmLastDate
fscDdmLastDate.description: Date of last recent reconfiguration in time_t (seconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00).

fscDdmCurrentStatus.name: fscDdmCurrentStatus
fscDdmCurrentStatus.description: Overall status of the driver, agent and the underlying objects. Possible values are: OK everything is fine DEGRADED at least one MultiPath or DuplexWrite group is in a degraded state (e.g. piece failed) ERROR software exception occured (software bug) FAILED communication with driver failed (e.g. driver not installed)

fscDdmInstallationType.name: fscDdmInstallationType
fscDdmInstallationType.description: Type of installed DuplexDataManager edition. Possible values are: DDMWIN PRIMERGY DuplexDataManager(R) (Windows) DDEWIN PRIMERGY easyMirror(TM) (Windows) MPWIN PRIMERGY MultiPath (Windows) DDMLX PRIMERGY DuplexDataManager(R) (Linux) DDELX PRIMERGY easyMirror(TM) (Linux) MPLX PRIMERGY MultiPath (Linux) UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwPieceTable.name: fscDdmDwPieceTable
fscDdmDwPieceTable.description: Table of all pieces DuplexWrite has detected.

fscDdmDwPiece.name: fscDdmDwPiece
fscDdmDwPiece.description: Entry in table of DuplexWrite pieces.

fscDdmDwIndex.name: fscDdmDwIndex
fscDdmDwIndex.description: Unique value for each DuplexWrite piece, starts at 0 and remains unchanged from one re-initialization of the agent to the next. Only used as index.

fscDdmDwDwPort.name: fscDdmDwDwPort
fscDdmDwDwPort.description: Virtual SCSI port number of the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwPath.name: fscDdmDwDwPath
fscDdmDwDwPath.description: Virtual SCSI path number of the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwTarget.name: fscDdmDwDwTarget
fscDdmDwDwTarget.description: Virtual SCSI target ID of the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwLun.name: fscDdmDwDwLun
fscDdmDwDwLun.description: Virtual SCSI LUN of the DuplexWrite group

fscDdmDwDwGroupNumber.name: fscDdmDwDwGroupNumber
fscDdmDwDwGroupNumber.description: Internal group number of the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwPieceNumber.name: fscDdmDwDwPieceNumber
fscDdmDwDwPieceNumber.description: Internal piece number in the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwSize.name: fscDdmDwDwSize
fscDdmDwDwSize.description: Size of the DuplexWrite group in MegaBytes.

fscDdmDwDwRoot.name: fscDdmDwDwRoot
fscDdmDwDwRoot.description: RootDisk flag of the DuplexWrite group. The RootDisk flag indicates special handling for boot/system disks. Possible values are: ON RootDisk flag is turned on OFF RootDisk flag is turned off UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwRecoverMode.name: fscDdmDwDwRecoverMode
fscDdmDwDwRecoverMode.description: Recover mode of the DuplexWrite groups. Possible values are: COPY during Recover all blocks are copied from one disk to another VERIFY during Recover blocks are read from all disks, compared and only written when a difference is detected DELTA during Recover only those areas of the disk are copied that were changed since the group broke up UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwStatus.name: fscDdmDwDwStatus
fscDdmDwDwStatus.description: Status of the DuplexWrite piece. Possible values are: ONLINE piece is working properly PREFERRED piece is working properly, used for read operations ERROR error occured during operation RECOVER data of the piece is updated from the other DISABLED operations on piece are stopped CLUSTER piece reserved by other cluster node HOTSPARE piece reserved as hotspare BROKEN piece was replaced by hotspare UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwReason.name: fscDdmDwDwReason
fscDdmDwDwReason.description: Reason why a status was set for the DuplexWrite piece. Possible values are: READFAILED read error WRITEFAILED write error RESERVATIONCONFLICT piece disabled because of SCSI reservation problems TIMEOUTOFSYNC piece disabled because timestamp was older than that of the other one HOSTOUTOFSYNC piece disabled because of different hostnames in DuplexWrite key STATUSOUTOFSYNC piece disabled because of ambiguous status USER status set by user WRITECONFIGFAILED COD could not be updated on disk READCONFIGFAILED COD could not be reread RECOVERREADFAILED data could not be read during recover process RECOVERWRITEFAILED data could not be written during recover process SPLITMIRROR piece disabled because second piece is configured but not accessible ONLINEPIECEFAILED piece disabled because the other (online) piece failed during recover SNAPSHOTINACTIVEPIECE piece disabled due to Snapshot ONLINEPIECEFORCED the more recent piece was set to online during boot PNPREMOVE PNP REMOVE request caused piece to be set to ERROR WRITEFLAG data is inconsistent - COD could not be synced after last WRITE DUPLICATESIGNATURE a duplicate signature was detected SIGNATURESAREWRONG signatures of both pieces of the DuplexWrite group are not the same BITMAPCOPIED piece was disabled after clone bitmap was copied to user GIVEUP give up this piece SPLITBRAIN disabled because a possible split brain situation was detected WRITEPROTECED this piece was disabled because the media is write protected PIECECONSERVED this piece is in status error, although it has the higher write counter - conserve it UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwActive.name: fscDdmDwDwActive
fscDdmDwDwActive.description: Active DuplexWrite piece for Snapshot. Possible values are: ON piece is an active piece for Snapshot OFF piece is not an active piece for Snapshot UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwRecoverProgress.name: fscDdmDwDwRecoverProgress
fscDdmDwDwRecoverProgress.description: Percentage of the Recover progress of the DuplexWrite piece. If no Recover is running the value is 0.

fscDdmDwDwHidden.name: fscDdmDwDwHidden
fscDdmDwDwHidden.description: Hidden flag for DuplexWrite piece. Possible values are: ON piece is hidden from the operating system (not claimable) OFF piece is not hidden UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwRecent.name: fscDdmDwDwRecent
fscDdmDwDwRecent.description: Recent flag for DuplexWrite piece. When no piece is Online the Recent flag indicates which piece was Online more recently. Possible values are: ON piece is the recent one OFF piece is not the recent one UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwForced.name: fscDdmDwDwForced
fscDdmDwDwForced.description: Forced flag for DuplexWrite piece. This flag indicates that the driver forced this piece Online during boot although it was not shutdown in status Online. Possible values are: ON piece was forced ONLINE during boot OFF piece was not forced ONLINE during boot UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwDwPieceCount.name: fscDdmDwDwPieceCount
fscDdmDwDwPieceCount.description: Number of configured pieces in the DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmDwDwPieceFound.name: fscDdmDwDwPieceFound
fscDdmDwDwPieceFound.description: Number of detected pieces in the DuplexWrite group

fscDdmDwDwBalance.name: fscDdmDwDwBalance
fscDdmDwDwBalance.description: Dynamic Diskload Balancing state of the DuplexWrite group. Possible values are: ON Dynamic Diskload Balancing is turned on OFF Dynamic Diskload Balancing is turned off UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwMpGroupNumber.name: fscDdmDwMpGroupNumber
fscDdmDwMpGroupNumber.description: Internal MultiPath group number of the DuplexWrite piece starting with 0.

fscDdmDwScPort.name: fscDdmDwScPort
fscDdmDwScPort.description: Real SCSI port number of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScPath.name: fscDdmDwScPath
fscDdmDwScPath.description: Real SCSI path number of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScTarget.name: fscDdmDwScTarget
fscDdmDwScTarget.description: Real SCSI target ID of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScLun.name: fscDdmDwScLun
fscDdmDwScLun.description: Real SCSI LUN of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScDiskNumber.name: fscDdmDwScDiskNumber
fscDdmDwScDiskNumber.description: Operating system assigned disk number of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScSize.name: fscDdmDwScSize
fscDdmDwScSize.description: Capacity of the DuplexWrite piece in MegaBytes.

fscDdmDwScSignature.name: fscDdmDwScSignature
fscDdmDwScSignature.description: Operating system assigned unique key (signature) of the DuplexWrite piece. If no signature is available the value is -1.

fscDdmDwScType.name: fscDdmDwScType
fscDdmDwScType.description: The SCSI type of the DuplexWrite piece. Possible values are: DISK direct access device TAPE tape device PRINTER printer device PROCESSOR processor device WORM write once read multiple device CDROM read only direct access device SCANNER scanner device OPTICALDISK optical device JUKEBOX medium changer NETWORK communication device UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmDwScInquiry.name: fscDdmDwScInquiry
fscDdmDwScInquiry.description: SCSI inquiry string (vendor and product id) of the DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmDwScResource.name: fscDdmDwScResource
fscDdmDwScResource.description: Cluster resource name of the DuplexWrite piece. Empty, if the piece is not a cluster resource.

fscDdmDwScNode.name: fscDdmDwScNode
fscDdmDwScNode.description: Cluster node name that owns the DuplexWrite piece. Empty, if the piece is not a cluster resource.

fscDdmDwScPciBus.name: fscDdmDwScPciBus
fscDdmDwScPciBus.description: PCI location of the controller (bus number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmDwScPciDevice.name: fscDdmDwScPciDevice
fscDdmDwScPciDevice.description: PCI location of the controller (device number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmDwScPciFunction.name: fscDdmDwScPciFunction
fscDdmDwScPciFunction.description: PCI location of the controller (function number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmDwScDriverName.name: fscDdmDwScDriverName
fscDdmDwScDriverName.description: Name of the driver that handles the controller.

fscDdmDwScDriverDescription.name: fscDdmDwScDriverDescription
fscDdmDwScDriverDescription.description: Description of the driver that handles the controller. Empty, if no description is available.

fscDdmMpPieceTable.name: fscDdmMpPieceTable
fscDdmMpPieceTable.description: Table of all paths MultiPath has detected.

fscDdmMpPiece.name: fscDdmMpPiece
fscDdmMpPiece.description: Entry in table of MultiPath paths.

fscDdmMpIndex.name: fscDdmMpIndex
fscDdmMpIndex.description: Unique value for each MultiPath path, starts at 0 and remains unchanged from one re-initialization of the agent to the next. Only used as index.

fscDdmMpMpPort.name: fscDdmMpMpPort
fscDdmMpMpPort.description: Virtual SCSI port number of the MultiPath group.

fscDdmMpMpPath.name: fscDdmMpMpPath
fscDdmMpMpPath.description: Virtual SCSI path number of the MultiPath group.

fscDdmMpMpTarget.name: fscDdmMpMpTarget
fscDdmMpMpTarget.description: Virtual SCSI target ID of the MultiPath group.

fscDdmMpMpLun.name: fscDdmMpMpLun
fscDdmMpMpLun.description: Virtual SCSI LUN of the MultiPath group.

fscDdmMpMpGroupNumber.name: fscDdmMpMpGroupNumber
fscDdmMpMpGroupNumber.description: Internal group number of the MultiPath group.

fscDdmMpMpAutoRecovery.name: fscDdmMpMpAutoRecovery
fscDdmMpMpAutoRecovery.description: AutoRecovery status of the MultiPath group. When AutoRecovery is turned on a repaired connection returns into a MultiPath group as Active or Standby otherwise it remains in status Error. Possible values are: ON AutoRecovery is turned on OFF AutoRecovery is turned off UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmMpMpAutoFailback.name: fscDdmMpMpAutoFailback
fscDdmMpMpAutoFailback.description: AutoFailback status of the MultiPath group. If AutoFailback is turned on a repaired connection returns into a MultiPath group in the state it was before the error occured. Possible values are: ON AutoFailback is turned on OFF AutoFailback is turned off UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmMpMpCabinetHandling.name: fscDdmMpMpCabinetHandling
fscDdmMpMpCabinetHandling.description: Connected storage type. If this cannot be detected the value is UNKNOWN. Possible values are: DEFAULT S40, JBOD CLARIION FibreCAT UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmMpMpStatus.name: fscDdmMpMpStatus
fscDdmMpMpStatus.description: Status of the MultiPath path. Possible values are: ACTIVE the piece can accept I/Os. When LoadBalancing is off only one path of a MultiPath group can be active STANDBY the path waits until an active path fails and takes over all I/Os then ERROR the path failed due to an error DISABLED the path is turned off - no I/O is possible UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmMpMpPreferred.name: fscDdmMpMpPreferred
fscDdmMpMpPreferred.description: Flag which path of a MultiPath group will be active after an error situation is cleared. This flag is only valid in case of AutoFailback. Possible values are: ON use the path as preferred MultiPath path OFF not marked as the preferred MultiPath path UNKNOWN none of the above

fscDdmMpDwName.name: fscDdmMpDwName
fscDdmMpDwName.description: Name of the DuplexWrite group where the MultiPath group is piece of. Empty, if the MultiPath group is not a member of a DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmMpDwGroupNumber.name: fscDdmMpDwGroupNumber
fscDdmMpDwGroupNumber.description: Internal DuplexWrite group number where the MultiPath group is piece of. -1, if the MultiPath group is not a member of a DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmMpScPort.name: fscDdmMpScPort
fscDdmMpScPort.description: Real SCSI port number of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScPath.name: fscDdmMpScPath
fscDdmMpScPath.description: Real SCSI path number of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScTarget.name: fscDdmMpScTarget
fscDdmMpScTarget.description: Real SCSI target ID of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScLun.name: fscDdmMpScLun
fscDdmMpScLun.description: Real SCSI LUN of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScDiskNumber.name: fscDdmMpScDiskNumber
fscDdmMpScDiskNumber.description: Operating system assigned disk number of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScSize.name: fscDdmMpScSize
fscDdmMpScSize.description: Capacity of the MultiPath path in MegaBytes.

fscDdmMpScSignature.name: fscDdmMpScSignature
fscDdmMpScSignature.description: Operating system assigned unique key (signature) of the MultiPath path. If the signature cannot be detected or is not available the value is -1.

fscDdmMpScType.name: fscDdmMpScType
fscDdmMpScType.description: The SCSI type of the MultiPath path. Possible values are: DISK direct access device TAPE tape device PRINTER printer device PROCESSOR processor device WORM write once read multiple device CDROM read only direct access device SCANNER scanner device OPTICALDISK optical device JUKEBOX medium changer NETWORK communication device UNKNOWN none of the above or cannot be detected

fscDdmMpScInquiry.name: fscDdmMpScInquiry
fscDdmMpScInquiry.description: SCSI inquiry string (vendor and product id) of the MultiPath path.

fscDdmMpScResource.name: fscDdmMpScResource
fscDdmMpScResource.description: Cluster resource name of the MultiPath path. Empty, if the piece is not a cluster resource.

fscDdmMpScNode.name: fscDdmMpScNode
fscDdmMpScNode.description: Cluster node name that owns the MultiPath path. Empty, if the piece is not a cluster resource.

fscDdmMpScPciBus.name: fscDdmMpScPciBus
fscDdmMpScPciBus.description: PCI location of the controller (bus number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmMpScPciDevice.name: fscDdmMpScPciDevice
fscDdmMpScPciDevice.description: PCI location of the controller (device number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmMpScPciFunction.name: fscDdmMpScPciFunction
fscDdmMpScPciFunction.description: PCI location of the controller (function number). -1 if the location cannot be detected.

fscDdmMpScDriverName.name: fscDdmMpScDriverName
fscDdmMpScDriverName.description: Name of the driver that handles the controller.

fscDdmMpScDriverDescription.name: fscDdmMpScDriverDescription
fscDdmMpScDriverDescription.description: Description of the driver that handles the controller. Empty, if no description is available.

fscDdmTrapServerName.name: fscDdmTrapServerName
fscDdmTrapServerName.description: Name of the server where the trap occured.

fscDdmTrapTime.name: fscDdmTrapTime
fscDdmTrapTime.description: Time the trap occured (in seconds since 1/1/1970 00:00:00).

fscDdmTrapPort.name: fscDdmTrapPort
fscDdmTrapPort.description: Physical SCSI port number where the change occured.

fscDdmTrapPath.name: fscDdmTrapPath
fscDdmTrapPath.description: Physical SCSI path number where the change occured.

fscDdmTrapTarget.name: fscDdmTrapTarget
fscDdmTrapTarget.description: Physical SCSI target ID where the change occured.

fscDdmTrapLun.name: fscDdmTrapLun
fscDdmTrapLun.description: Physical SCSI LUN where the change occured.

fscDdmNewConfig.name: fscDdmNewConfig
fscDdmNewConfig.description: The driver has created a new DuplexWrite group or has added a new piece to an existing DuplexWrite group as requested by the user.

fscDdmPieceRemoved.name: fscDdmPieceRemoved
fscDdmPieceRemoved.description: The driver has removed a piece from a DuplexWrite group as requested by the user.

fscDdmConfigRemoved.name: fscDdmConfigRemoved
fscDdmConfigRemoved.description: The driver has removed a DuplexWrite group as requested by the user.

fscDdmStatusSet.name: fscDdmStatusSet
fscDdmStatusSet.description: The driver has set the status of a DuplexWrite piece as requested by the user.

fscDdmUpdateStatus.name: fscDdmUpdateStatus
fscDdmUpdateStatus.description: The driver has updated the status of a DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmPieceRecovered.name: fscDdmPieceRecovered
fscDdmPieceRecovered.description: The driver has successfully recovered a DuplexWrite group. Both pieces are ONLINE.

fscDdmRecoverAborted.name: fscDdmRecoverAborted
fscDdmRecoverAborted.description: The driver has aborted the recover process of a DuplexWrite group as requested by the user.

fscDdmReservationConflict.name: fscDdmReservationConflict
fscDdmReservationConflict.description: The driver has detected a reservation conflict. A whole DuplexWrite group is not accessible from now on. This is only an error if it happens during operation (not initialization) of the group and if the group is not on another cluster node.

fscDdmConfigChanged.name: fscDdmConfigChanged
fscDdmConfigChanged.description: The driver has done a rescan/reread and found a new configuration.

fscDdmConfigInvalidated.name: fscDdmConfigInvalidated
fscDdmConfigInvalidated.description: The driver has invalidated the configuration information for a DuplexWrite group. The configuration information is reread before the next access of the DuplexWrite group on this cluster element.

fscDdmActiveLunChanged.name: fscDdmActiveLunChanged
fscDdmActiveLunChanged.description: The driver has selected a specified piece of a DuplexWrite group for read commands.

fscDdmPieceFailed.name: fscDdmPieceFailed
fscDdmPieceFailed.description: The driver has detected an error on a DuplexWrite piece.

fscDdmRootFlagChanged.name: fscDdmRootFlagChanged
fscDdmRootFlagChanged.description: The driver has changed the root behavior of a DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmForceActive.name: fscDdmForceActive
fscDdmForceActive.description: The driver has marked a disk of a DuplexWrite group forced active at next boot. The partner disk can be used as Snapshot.

fscDdmNameChanged.name: fscDdmNameChanged
fscDdmNameChanged.description: The driver has changed the name of a DuplexWrite group.

fscDdmPathFailed.name: fscDdmPathFailed
fscDdmPathFailed.description: The driver has detected an error on one path of a MultiPath group.

fscDdmRetry.name: fscDdmRetry
fscDdmRetry.description: The driver has detected an error on one path of a MultiPath group and the retry of the command was successful on another path.

fscDdmActivePortChanged.name: fscDdmActivePortChanged
fscDdmActivePortChanged.description: The driver has changed the active path of a MultiPath group.

fscDdmReconfigured.name: fscDdmReconfigured
fscDdmReconfigured.description: The driver has detected a MultiPath configuration change.

fscDdmStatusChanged.name: fscDdmStatusChanged
fscDdmStatusChanged.description: The MultiPath status has changed.\nThe user has activated, disabled, ... the MultiPath path, or changed the failover policy.\nThe path has changed as request of MultiPath AutoBalance.

fscDdmAutoRecovered.name: fscDdmAutoRecovered
fscDdmAutoRecovered.description: The driver has enabled a path of a MultiPath group (AutoRecovery).

fscDdmErrorCleared.name: fscDdmErrorCleared
fscDdmErrorCleared.description: The error of MultiPath path is cleared and reused (AutoFailback).

fscDdmPnPRemove.name: fscDdmPnPRemove
fscDdmPnPRemove.description: A Plug and Play Removal of an device was detected.

fscDdmPnPNew.name: fscDdmPnPNew
fscDdmPnPNew.description: A Plug and Play Add of an device was detected.

fscDdmCluster.description: The DuplexDataManager service has detected a cluster configuration change.
